<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <meta name="description" content="Very Good AdBlock is a polished, performant, minimal, modern Chrome MV3 ad blocker for pop-ups, YouTube, Twitch, and ad protection.">
    <title>Very Good AdBlock - Immediate, Modern Ad Protection</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/styles.css">
  </head>
  <body class="marketing-shell">
    <header class="marketing-nav" aria-label="Primary navigation">
      <a class="brand-lockup" href="#top" aria-label="Very Good AdBlock home">
        <span class="brand-mark" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        <span>Very Good AdBlock</span>
      </a>
      <nav>
        <a href="#features">Features</a>
        <a href="#stats">Stats</a>
        <a href="#privacy">Privacy</a>
      </nav>
      <a class="nav-action" href="docs/">Read docs</a>
    </header>

    <main id="top">
      <section class="marketing-hero">
        <div class="hero-copy">
          <p class="eyebrow">Chrome MV3 ad blocker</p>
          <h1>Very Good AdBlock</h1>
          <p class="hero-lede">
            A polished, performant, minimal, modern Chrome MV3 ad blocker for immediate pop-up, YouTube, Twitch,
            and ad protection. Built to stay fast while removing intrusive interruptions before they take over the page.
          </p>
          <div class="hero-actions">
            <a class="primary-link" href="docs/guide/install">Install locally</a>
            <a class="secondary-link" href="#features">See protection</a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="hero-product" aria-label="Very Good AdBlock product preview">
          <div class="browser-preview">
            <div class="browser-bar">
              <span></span>
              <span></span>
              <span></span>
              <strong>youtube.com/watch</strong>
            </div>
            <div class="watch-preview">
              <div class="video-surface">
                <div class="skip-badge">Video ad skipped · 0:27 saved</div>
                <div class="play-ring"></div>
              </div>
              <div class="feed-lines">
                <span class="line wide"></span>
                <span class="line"></span>
                <span class="line short"></span>
                <span class="blocked-chip">3 sponsored placements removed</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <aside class="hero-popup-preview">
            <div class="preview-topline">
              <span>Protection active</span>
              <strong>98%</strong>
            </div>
            <div class="preview-stats">
              <div>
                <strong>1,248</strong>
                <span>blocked today</span>
              </div>
              <div>
                <strong>312 MB</strong>
                <span>data saved</span>
              </div>
              <div>
                <strong>41 min</strong>
                <span>video time</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="mini-bars" aria-hidden="true">
              <span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span>
              <span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span>
            </div>
          </aside>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="features" class="marketing-band">
        <div class="section-kicker">
          <p class="eyebrow">Coverage</p>
          <h2>Immediate protection without fragile page rewrites.</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-grid">
          <article>
            <span class="feature-icon network" aria-hidden="true"></span>
            <h3>Network blocking</h3>
            <p>Manifest V3 declarative rules stop known ad, tracker, popup, and annoyance hosts before requests complete.</p>
          </article>
          <article>
            <span class="feature-icon video" aria-hidden="true"></span>
            <h3>YouTube and Twitch helpers</h3>
            <p>Hides YouTube feed, masthead, and display ads, clicks available skip controls, and detects Twitch video-ad markers — without ever touching the player or real videos.</p>
          </article>
          <article>
            <span class="feature-icon social" aria-hidden="true"></span>
            <h3>Social ad blocking</h3>
            <p>Blocks known promoted-content and ad request paths through MV3 rules, plus site-specific cosmetic hiding for promoted feed entries.</p>
          </article>
          <article>
            <span class="feature-icon control" aria-hidden="true"></span>
            <h3>One-click control</h3>
            <p>Pause protection per site, customize the ad experience with allowlists, and inspect diagnostics from a minimal modern dashboard.</p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="stats" class="stats-showcase">
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow">Receipts</p>
          <h2>Modern local stats make blocking visible over time.</h2>
          <p>
            Very Good AdBlock tracks lifetime ads blocked, daily history, estimated bandwidth saved, and estimated video minutes recovered.
            Sync-backed totals can follow a user into a new install while detailed histories stay local.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-wall" aria-label="Very Good AdBlock stats examples">
          <article>
            <strong>52,910</strong>
            <span>lifetime blocks</span>
          </article>
          <article>
            <strong>8.4 GB</strong>
            <span>estimated data saved</span>
          </article>
          <article>
            <strong>19.6 hr</strong>
            <span>estimated video time saved</span>
          </article>
          <article>
            <strong>0</strong>
            <span>remote telemetry events</span>
          </article>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="privacy" class="privacy-band">
        <div class="privacy-copy">
          <p class="eyebrow">Privacy</p>
          <h2>No hidden telemetry. No remote rule surprises.</h2>
          <p>
            Rules ship with releases, user site choices become local dynamic rules, and the dashboard clearly marks estimates.
            The point is simple: remove the obstruction immediately while keeping the extension performant, minimal, and user-controlled.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="privacy-list">
          <div><span></span>Chrome MV3 declarativeNetRequest</div>
          <div><span></span>Site-specific cosmetic hiding, kill switch included</div>
          <div><span></span>Local and sync storage split</div>
          <div><span></span>Exportable stats and reset controls</div>
        </div>
      </section>
    </main>

    <footer class="marketing-footer">
      <span>Very Good AdBlock</span>
      <a href="docs/">Docs</a>
      <a href="docs/guide/usage">Usage</a>
    </footer>
  </body>
</html>
